00:47.215 --> 00:50.552
<font color="#808080">SIMON:</font> <i>There is a painting,
it's by Rembrandt.</i>

00:51.177 --> 00:53.846
<i>'Storm On The Sea Of Galilee',
it's called...</i>

00:54.389 --> 00:56.224
<i>...and he's in it.</i>

00:56.516 --> 00:59.477
<i>Old Rembrandt,
he's in the painting.</i>

00:59.602 --> 01:01.896
<i>He's in there, right in
the middle of the storm,</i>

01:01.980 --> 01:03.606
<i>looking straight out at you.</i>

01:03.731 --> 01:06.109
<i>But... you can't see him.</i>

01:06.234 --> 01:07.902
<i>And the reason
you can't see him</i>

01:07.986 --> 01:09.862
<i>is because
the painting has been stolen.</i>

01:09.988 --> 01:12.782
<i>Lots of paintings have been stolen.
They're still missing.</i>

01:12.907 --> 01:15.743
'Pride Of Lions' showing here on my left.
Thank you.

01:15.868 --> 01:18.079
I start the bidding here
at a thousand guineas.

01:18.204 --> 01:21.666
<font color="#808080">SIMON:</font> <i>It used to be anyone
could steal a painting.</i>

01:22.041 --> 01:23.209
<i>There was no need for a gun.</i>

01:23.293 --> 01:24.335
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN SCREAMS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

01:25.044 --> 01:28.047
<i>All it took was a bit of
muscle and some nerve.</i>

01:28.840 --> 01:30.174
<i>And that...</i>

01:31.342 --> 01:33.678
<i>...was that.</i>

01:36.639 --> 01:39.684
<i>But not anymore.
Those days are gone.</i>

01:40.059 --> 01:42.145
<i>A business can't function
taking big hits</i>

01:42.228 --> 01:44.480
<i>like that.
So now we have procedures...</i>

01:44.606 --> 01:46.983
<i>...and precautions
and security measures.</i>

01:47.108 --> 01:49.485
<i>Now we have a policy.</i>

01:50.194 --> 01:55.199
<i>We have bag searches and magnetic
alarms and silent scanners...</i>

01:55.325 --> 01:57.577
<i>...and X-ray machines
and cameras.</i>

01:57.702 --> 02:01.080
<i>Also we have drills. And the
first thing they tell us is...</i>

02:01.372 --> 02:03.916
Do not be a hero.
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR THUDS)</font>

02:05.585 --> 02:07.962
This is a robbery!

02:09.505 --> 02:13.468
Now no piece of art
is worth a human life.

02:14.761 --> 02:16.304
<font color="#808080">SIMON:</font> <i>It's a sound
piece of advice, that.</i>

02:16.387 --> 02:19.182
<i>No piece of art is
worth a human life.</i>

02:21.976 --> 02:23.227
<i>But...</i>

02:23.353 --> 02:25.480
<i>...in the event of an event...</i>

02:26.314 --> 02:29.442
<i>...or situation we are to remove
the most valuable item...</i>

02:30.485 --> 02:33.279
<i>...or items and take them
to a place of safety.</i>

02:33.696 --> 02:35.948
<i>I.E., the fast-drop slot...</i>

02:36.407 --> 02:38.368
<i>...in a time delay vault.</i>

02:38.493 --> 02:40.662
That's about all
you can do really.

02:40.745 --> 02:42.455
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT TALKING)</font>

02:42.538 --> 02:43.873
Come and enjoy the auction.

02:43.998 --> 02:47.877
<i>I mean, if you wanna let people
in, if you want them to bid...</i>

02:48.002 --> 02:49.337
<i>And when you're
trying to flog the star</i>

02:49.420 --> 02:52.006
<i>of the show for
25 million sterling...</i>

02:52.298 --> 02:54.801
<i>you definitely
want them to bid.</i>

02:54.926 --> 02:58.221
Â£650,000.

02:59.555 --> 03:02.684
Sold to paddle 88.
Congratulations, madam.

03:03.142 --> 03:04.811
Ladies and gentlemen...

03:04.936 --> 03:07.397
...there will now
be a brief interval.

03:07.522 --> 03:11.984
When we reconvene, our head
auctioneer, Francis Lemaitre...

03:12.110 --> 03:16.030
...will lead the auction for
Goya's 'Witches In The Air'.

03:16.698 --> 03:17.740
Thank you very much.

03:19.867 --> 03:20.868
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

03:21.327 --> 03:23.705
<i>So we notify the cops
about big ticket sales...</i>

03:23.830 --> 03:27.709
<i>...and we even keep half a dozen
Ukrainian ex-naval commandos...</i>

03:27.834 --> 03:32.004
<i>...in a van outside, just in case
it all kicks off. Or so they say.</i>

03:33.214 --> 03:35.883
Simon, are you coming?
I'm about to start.

03:37.301 --> 03:38.302
Uh...

03:38.928 --> 03:40.012
Yeah.

03:40.888 --> 03:42.223
Here we go.

03:43.349 --> 03:45.393
<i>So, what happens,
of course, is that</i>

03:45.476 --> 03:48.187
<i>just as we up our game,
the villains up theirs.</i>

03:48.312 --> 03:50.398
<i>They don't just
turn up on spec anymore.</i>

03:50.481 --> 03:53.234
<i>We have precautions,
they have plans.</i>

03:53.359 --> 03:55.528
<i>They do research,
they do recces.</i>

03:55.611 --> 03:57.864
<i>They learn about our
cameras and scanners...</i>

03:57.989 --> 04:02.243
<i>...and Ukrainian ex-naval commandos
but some things don't change.</i>

04:02.368 --> 04:05.705
It still takes muscle
and it still takes nerve.

04:06.247 --> 04:09.959
Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen,
and welcome to Delancy's.

04:10.084 --> 04:12.920
We are extremely
honored to be selling

04:13.004 --> 04:15.840
Francisco de Goya's
wonderful work...

04:15.965 --> 04:17.800
...of 'Witches In The Air'.

04:17.925 --> 04:20.178
Goya, the father
of modern art...

04:20.303 --> 04:23.097
...and the first great painter
of the human mind.

04:23.222 --> 04:27.310
Let's start the bidding
at 5 million pounds.

04:27.435 --> 04:29.604
Thank you, sir. 5 million pounds.
An opening bid.

04:29.729 --> 04:31.773
5 million, 500 thousand.
6 million.

04:38.321 --> 04:40.615
In the center here
at 10 million pounds.

04:41.073 --> 04:43.075
11 million on the aisle.

04:43.201 --> 04:45.828
12 million. 13 million.

04:51.042 --> 04:53.669
17 million. Thank you, sir.
18 million.

04:56.631 --> 04:58.758
19 million. Bad luck. 20?

05:02.345 --> 05:05.097
21 million pounds.
Take your time.

05:05.223 --> 05:06.599
22 million. Thank you.

05:26.160 --> 05:29.914
Telephone bidder now. 26 million.
26 on the telephone.

05:30.039 --> 05:32.166
27 to the lady on the aisle.

05:32.291 --> 05:33.626
Small one?
Small one.

05:33.751 --> 05:36.087
27 million,
500 thousand I'll take.

05:38.130 --> 05:40.591
Last chance.
Hammer's coming down.

05:40.716 --> 05:44.387
I'm selling for 27 million,
500 thousand pounds.

05:44.595 --> 05:46.931
Sold. Paddle number 104.

05:49.475 --> 05:50.852
Get down! Get down!

05:52.436 --> 05:53.437
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL APPLAUDING)</font>

